doesn't want to change anything.

04:30.534 --> 04:31.910
So, kind of bad.

04:33.329 --> 04:34.871
How was Miami?

04:35.122 --> 04:36.533
Fine. Lonesome.

04:36.791 --> 04:38.782
Couldn't pay me enough
to live down there.

04:39.084 --> 04:40.661
Then why'd you go?

04:41.127 --> 04:44.294
Senator Michaelson
has powerfuI friends.

04:50.011 --> 04:52.087
Hello, Cinderella.

04:52.806 --> 04:54.882
Did you miss me?
I sure missed you.

04:55.141 --> 04:56.683
Oh, that's my girI.

04:56.935 --> 04:59.260
She missed you.
I missed you.

05:00.772 --> 05:02.052
You been smoking?

05:03.608 --> 05:05.268
Smoking? I'm not smoking.

05:06.528 --> 05:08.319
Come on, honey.

05:08.947 --> 05:10.489
You reek of it.

05:11.241 --> 05:14.075
Amy, I've been sitting around
in bars following this guy.

05:14.326 --> 05:16.200
Is this the first thing I get?

05:16.412 --> 05:19.116
- You're accusing me?
- I'm not accusing you.

05:20.124 --> 05:23.078
I'm not smoking, okay?
We've been all through that.

05:24.169 --> 05:26.328
I'll make dinner.
Are you hungry?

05:26.588 --> 05:27.502
You're cooking?

05:32.012 --> 05:34.170
I missed you.

05:39.519 --> 05:41.844
I don't like it when you leave.

05:46.651 --> 05:48.110
Should I go?

05:48.695 --> 05:50.188
I'm going to do it.

06:01.832 --> 06:03.113
Come on.

06:03.375 --> 06:06.210
What's all the trouble, Cinderella?

06:06.921 --> 06:08.545
There, there.

06:17.431 --> 06:19.389
I love you.

06:22.354 --> 06:23.729
I love you.

06:37.284 --> 06:39.443
Honey, phone!

06:48.213 --> 06:49.790
Okay, I've got it!

06:50.048 --> 06:52.717
Sorry, I was just switching phones.

06:56.596 --> 06:59.052
It's a pleasure to make
your acquaintance, Mr. Longdale.

06:59.307 --> 07:01.465
How can I be of assistance to you?

07:06.897 --> 07:08.806
Four o'clock would be fine.

07:12.987 --> 07:14.896
I think I know where it is.

07:55.902 --> 07:58.475
DanieI Longdale.
We spoke on the phone.

07:58.738 --> 07:59.568
Pleasure.

07:59.781 --> 08:02.900
I'm the Christians' attorney and
an executor of the estate.

08:03.159 --> 08:04.238
This is Mrs. Christian.

08:04.494 --> 08:06.202
An honour to meet you.

08:06.496 --> 08:08.821
You come highly
recommended, Mr. Welles.

08:09.082 --> 08:13.125
I've spoken to associates of mine in
Harrisburg, Lancaster and Hershey.

08:13.335 --> 08:14.912
You have influentiaI friends.

08:15.128 --> 08:18.083
I've been privileged to provide
services for people I admire.

08:18.299 --> 08:20.755
You were praised
for your discretion...

08:21.010 --> 08:24.344
...your strict adherence
to confidentiality.

08:24.597 --> 08:25.427
Thank you.

08:28.684 --> 08:31.769
As you know,
my husband passed away recently.

08:32.020 --> 08:34.227
My condolences, Mrs. Christian.

08:34.440 --> 08:39.565
His passing has left me
with something of a dilemma.

08:39.986 --> 08:42.110
I'll do whatever I can to help.

08:43.073 --> 08:45.363
My husband's inner sanctum.

08:45.618 --> 08:48.322
Not many people have been
inside this room.

08:50.831 --> 08:52.622
My father worked the Pittsburgh mill.

08:52.874 --> 08:55.081
Irving United SteeI, I believe.

08:55.335 --> 08:57.743
But you attended Penn
on an academic scholarship.

08:57.963 --> 08:59.077
That's right.

08:59.297 --> 09:01.835
Peers went into law and finance.
You chose surveillance.

09:02.050 --> 09:03.877
I decided it was the future.

09:04.345 --> 09:05.839
Your husband is a legend.

09:06.139 --> 09:07.088
Please.

09:07.348 --> 09:09.886
We were married 45 years.

09:10.143 --> 09:13.393
Four children, seven grandchildren.

09:13.855 --> 09:15.563
But his true passion lay...

09:15.773 --> 09:17.054
...in his work.

09:17.317 --> 09:19.143
But he was always loyaI.

09:19.360 --> 09:22.396
I loved him deeply.

09:22.821 --> 09:24.280
I understand.

09:26.658 --> 09:28.034
DanieI.

09:28.744 --> 09:32.409
My husband was the only one
with the combination to this safe.

09:32.622 --> 09:34.282
We hired somebody to open it.

09:34.708 --> 09:36.747
I prevented anyone...

09:36.960 --> 09:39.167
...from seeing the contents.

09:39.379 --> 09:42.464
I felt these were
my husband's private things.

09:42.758 --> 09:43.837
I didn't...

09:45.636 --> 09:47.675
I didn't realize...

09:48.513 --> 09:50.839
Do you want to tell me
what you found?

09:53.477 --> 09:55.469
Cash, stock certificates.

09:55.687 --> 09:59.980
Nothing out of the ordinary,
really, except that.

10:01.901 --> 10:03.015
It's a film...

10:05.237 --> 10:07.360
...where a girI appears to be murdered.

10:07.573 --> 10:09.317
I'm not sure I understand.

10:09.575 --> 10:11.153
It's very realistic.

10:11.369 --> 10:14.572
But how many people seem to be
realistically killed...

10:14.789 --> 10:16.700
...in movies and on TV every day?

10:17.585 --> 10:21.203
It begins as a relatively
sleazy bit of pornography...

10:21.464 --> 10:24.465
...and rapidly turns
quite violent and bloody.

10:29.764 --> 10:32.516
What you're talking about
is called a snuff film.

10:32.725 --> 10:35.050
Snuff films are a kind of urban myth.

10:35.811 --> 10:38.646
Sex industry folkIore.
There's no such thing.

10:38.897 --> 10:40.689
That's what I explained
to Mrs. Christian.

10:40.899 --> 10:43.390
This is probably
an S & M film of some sort.

10:43.652 --> 10:45.609
Simulated rape, simulated violence.

10:45.863 --> 10:48.104
It's hard to stomach,
but there are ways of doing it.

10:48.365 --> 10:49.943
Fake blood, speciaI effects.

10:50.158 --> 10:53.362
Would you look at the film
and give us your opinion?

10:53.996 --> 10:55.158
AII I want...

10:55.372 --> 10:59.666
...is to know that
this atrocity is false.

11:00.294 --> 11:02.002
I want the proof.

12:57.242 --> 12:58.108
Well...

12:58.368 --> 13:01.488
...whoever made the film
was adept at authenticity.

13:01.747 --> 13:05.412
But I'm no expert.
Let the police make a determination.

13:05.625 --> 13:06.455
Out of the question.

13:06.710 --> 13:09.462
That'd be so unnecessary
for any number of reasons...

13:09.713 --> 13:12.880
...not the least of which is
Mr. Christian's reputation.

13:14.468 --> 13:16.377
Find out who made this film...

13:16.636 --> 13:18.428
...and establish whether it's reaI.

13:18.847 --> 13:20.222
You can name your price.

13:20.474 --> 13:24.258
You'll be provided with
whatever you need to buy information.

13:26.647 --> 13:28.556
GirI's all I've got to go on.

13:28.815 --> 13:30.606
I could treat it
like a missing persons case.

13:30.816 --> 13:31.730
Understood.

13:31.984 --> 13:32.933
Of course...

13:33.194 --> 13:36.894
...we need to be assured
that you would not copy this film.

13:37.156 --> 13:38.947
You have my word on that.

13:39.408 --> 13:41.401
But I'll be dealing
directly with you...

13:41.619 --> 13:42.568
...and only you.

13:42.828 --> 13:44.655
Your relationship with
your attorney is your own.

13:44.872 --> 13:46.829
- No offense.
- None taken.

13:47.083 --> 13:50.334
I realize you've given this
carefuI consideration.

13:52.130 --> 13:53.293
You could have destroyed it.

13:53.507 --> 13:56.128
Tell me the poor girI wasn't killed.

13:56.343 --> 13:57.671
Please?

13:57.928 --> 13:59.755
Find her alive.

14:00.013 --> 14:02.172
I'll do the best I can, ma'am.

14:43.556 --> 14:44.386
Cleveland?

14:44.599 --> 14:45.630
You just got home.

14:45.892 --> 14:48.596
I wish I could stay,
but this is the mortgage.

14:48.853 --> 14:50.312
It's Cindy's college money.

14:50.563 --> 14:52.805
If I do right by her,
with the circle she runs in...

14:53.065 --> 14:54.476
...this could be a big break.

14:54.734 --> 14:56.109
Do we need a break?

14:56.319 --> 14:58.311
Your father thinks we do.

15:01.033 --> 15:04.152
So, what was Mrs. Christian like?

15:04.411 --> 15:07.910
Like you'd expect, I guess.
I feeI sorry for her.

15:08.165 --> 15:09.196
It's a missing persons.

15:09.416 --> 15:12.084
I told her I'd give it
a couple of weeks. Three.

15:12.793 --> 15:15.830
It can't take longer than that.
It's an outside shot.

15:16.088 --> 15:20.168
That's all I can tell you.
Sometimes you can't know what I'm doing.

15:20.884 --> 15:22.711
It's always that way.

15:24.054 --> 15:27.387
- She's awake. I'll get her.
- I'll be up in a sec.

15:56.293 --> 15:58.333
- You're taking the gun?
- I won't need it.

15:58.546 --> 15:59.376
Don't take it.

15:59.630 --> 16:02.417
I won't wear it.
It's a precaution. Don't worry.

16:02.675 --> 16:05.296
Will you call me
when you get there, please?

16:21.028 --> 16:25.157
I've been hired by a couple in
Philadelphia, a doctor and his wife.

16:25.408 --> 16:28.657
A few days ago, they picked up
a girl hitchhiking off 81...

16:28.910 --> 16:30.986
...a runaway, about 18, maybe.

16:31.246 --> 16:34.995
They buy her a meal.
The doctor tries to convince her...

16:35.250 --> 16:37.456
...that, at least,
she should call home.

16:37.711 --> 16:40.249
Not surprisingly, the girl ate,
excused herself...

16:40.464 --> 16:42.088
...that was the last they saw of her.

16:42.340 --> 16:45.507
We had a friend of mine
at the department work up a sketch.

16:45.844 --> 16:47.967
They want to see
if I can I.D. this girI...

16:48.221 --> 16:50.344
...then pass along
a message to the parents...

16:50.599 --> 16:52.638
...letting them know
the kid's alive.

16:53.727 --> 16:55.636
You don't mind if I run a check?

16:55.854 --> 16:57.182
Go ahead.

16:58.148 --> 17:00.639
You want it, you got it.
Knock yourself out.

17:00.901 --> 17:04.269
Anywhere from 850,000 to 1,000,000
missing every year.

17:04.528 --> 17:07.980
We got as much as we can on computer,
then it's the wet-thumb method.

17:08.199 --> 17:10.523
Files are by state
and year of disappearance.

17:10.785 --> 17:13.323
Children are separate.
No eating or smoking.

17:13.579 --> 17:15.323
- There's coffee.
- Any good?

17:15.539 --> 17:16.654
Horrible.

17:16.915 --> 17:18.873
It'll be your best friend
after a few days...

17:19.126 --> 17:20.667
...if you last that long.

17:20.920 --> 17:22.118
Good luck.

17:26.009 --> 17:27.338
Honey, it's me.

17:27.594 --> 17:28.424
How are you?

17:28.679 --> 17:29.710
I'm good.

17:29.972 --> 17:30.920
Where are you?

17:31.181 --> 17:34.016
I'm still in Cleveland.
How's Cindy?

17:34.267 --> 17:37.304
She's sweet.
She's sleeping.

17:37.688 --> 17:41.020
- I'm missing you bigtime.
- Yeah, I miss you too.

17:41.899 --> 17:43.892
I'll call you tomorrow night.

17:44.610 --> 17:45.808
Good night.

17:46.028 --> 17:47.772
Good night, sweetheart.

18:31.949 --> 18:34.073
Hello, Mrs. Christian?
Tom Welles.

18:34.328 --> 18:35.526
Here's where we stand.

18:35.787 --> 18:39.203
I checked the film stock.
It's called Supralux 5-4-4.

18:39.458 --> 18:43.041
The company that made that
stock discontinued it in '92.

18:43.253 --> 18:45.625
So the film was made prior to that?

18:45.839 --> 18:48.674
Yes. I'm probably being
overly thorough with this...

18:48.926 --> 18:52.091
...but you might dig up your husband's
financiaI records...

18:52.345 --> 18:53.969
...about 6 or 7 years ago.

18:54.222 --> 18:56.891
See if there's anything
out of the ordinary.

18:57.099 --> 19:00.718
This isn't a movie you drop off
at the one-hour photo.

19:00.937 --> 19:02.728
So you think it's one of a kind.

19:02.980 --> 19:06.396
The film is what we've got.
There's no negative.

19:07.026 --> 19:09.775
Unlike video, it's not
designed to be duplicated.

19:10.026 --> 19:12.102
Whatever this is,
I have a feeling...

19:12.362 --> 19:15.279
...there aren't many copies
floating around, if any.

19:15.490 --> 19:19.155
I'm looking for a girl
we're not even sure is missing.

19:19.410 --> 19:22.115
With this happening 6 or 7 years ago...

19:22.372 --> 19:26.582
...finding the guys who made this film
is going to be very difficult.

19:26.834 --> 19:29.870
I know you can do it.
You're doing a wonderful job.

19:30.129 --> 19:33.248
Please tell me you'll
continue the investigation.

19:33.507 --> 19:35.546
I will. I'll keep trying for you.

19:35.759 --> 19:38.297
You can count on me.
Goodbye, Mrs. Christian.

19:39.721 --> 19:44.016
We can't come to the phone now,
so please leave a message at the beep.

19:44.269 --> 19:45.300
Honey, it's me.

19:45.520 --> 19:48.521
I'm sorry I forgot
to call last night.

19:48.773 --> 19:50.398
I won't forget tonight.

19:50.650 --> 19:53.485
I've been gone a long time.
I hope I'll be home soon.

19:53.736 --> 19:56.572
I love you, and I miss you.
We'll talk tonight.

21:18.862 --> 21:20.820
You looking for Janet?

21:27.413 --> 21:29.370
Hello, Mrs. Mathews?

21:29.581 --> 21:32.203
I'm Thomas Hart.
I'm a licensed investigator.

21:32.501 --> 21:35.952
I've been hired by the U.S. Resource
Centre, Missing Persons...

21:36.213 --> 21:37.791
...as part of an internaI audit.

21:38.048 --> 21:43.173
I'd like you to answer questions
about your daughter, Mary Anne.

21:43.429 --> 21:47.591
I spoke to your FBI contact
yesterday, Agent...

21:47.849 --> 21:49.343
NeiI. NeiI Cole?

21:49.600 --> 21:53.894
Yes, Agent Cole. He told me
he'd call and let you know to expect me.

21:54.647 --> 21:56.355
He didn't call?

22:02.614 --> 22:03.444
Is this you?

22:05.702 --> 22:07.741
You look about five years old.

22:08.204 --> 22:09.070
A little older.

22:09.331 --> 22:10.529
Sweet.

22:13.585 --> 22:18.710
It's important that you don't
let this raise your expectations.

22:19.215 --> 22:22.466
It's not going to effect
any ongoing efforts.

22:23.218 --> 22:25.211
AII I'm saying is, please know...

22:25.471 --> 22:28.222
...I'm not here to create
any false hope.

22:32.102 --> 22:35.222
We fought all the time,
Mary Anne and me...

22:35.481 --> 22:36.643
...and her stepdad.

22:36.899 --> 22:38.559
She hated him...

22:38.817 --> 22:40.893
...because he wasn't her reaI dad.

22:41.570 --> 22:44.571
Trouble here, trouble at schooI.

22:44.823 --> 22:45.938
Trouble.

22:46.450 --> 22:50.068
Didn't like rules.
Takes after me, I guess.

22:50.329 --> 22:52.571
I had to learn the hard way.

22:54.166 --> 22:55.910
Can I speak to your husband?

22:56.168 --> 22:57.082
Her stepfather?

22:57.336 --> 22:58.367
Dave?

22:58.628 --> 22:59.956
Gone.

23:00.421 --> 23:02.794
Two years after Mary Anne left.

23:03.174 --> 23:06.210
All the time, she resented him.

23:06.468 --> 23:10.252
I lost her because of him,
and then I lost him.

23:10.848 --> 23:13.006
I'm the only one still here.

23:14.434 --> 23:16.261
Did Mary have a boyfriend?

23:16.521 --> 23:19.142
She was sneaking out with someone.

23:19.524 --> 23:21.481
She wouldn't tell me who.

23:21.776 --> 23:25.110
Coming home with hickeys,
Iying all the time.

23:26.823 --> 23:30.239
I am sorry to bring this up,
but in these circumstances...

23:30.493 --> 23:32.118
...with the stepfather...

23:32.370 --> 23:35.489
...were there any indications
of any sort of abuse?

23:35.831 --> 23:38.748
There was nothing like that.
The police and FBI asked.

23:39.001 --> 23:42.251
There wasn't anything like that.
She'd have told me.

23:42.463 --> 23:45.167
I apologize. I had to ask.

23:46.300 --> 23:50.712
Those are for her birthday.
One for every year she missed.

23:50.971 --> 23:53.640
They'll be waiting for her
when she comes back.

23:55.684 --> 23:57.641
It's because I slapped her.

23:59.396 --> 24:00.511
I know.

24:02.316 --> 24:06.611
We was fighting about Dave,
and she was just pushing my buttons.

24:06.863 --> 24:08.238
And I slapped her.

24:10.199 --> 24:11.397
Jesus!

24:12.826 --> 24:14.107
Next day, she was gone.

24:15.412 --> 24:18.199
When kids run, they
almost always leave a note.

24:18.457 --> 24:19.572
It's guilt, usually.

24:19.833 --> 24:21.541
There wasn't one.

24:21.835 --> 24:22.950
Police looked.

24:23.212 --> 24:25.833
An abduction's one thing,
a runaway's another.

24:26.090 --> 24:29.376
Sometimes it's not the priority
for the police it should be.

24:29.677 --> 24:33.841
There wasn't anything.
Don't you think I wish there was?

24:34.182 --> 24:36.638
You're probably right,
but would you let me look?

24:38.520 --> 24:40.097
You tell me...

24:40.355 --> 24:42.561
...not to get my hopes up...

24:43.066 --> 24:46.066
...not to raise my expectations.

24:50.114 --> 24:51.442
Go ahead.

24:51.990 --> 24:53.401
I need a drink.

24:54.743 --> 24:56.072
Thank you.

26:44.435 --> 26:46.262
Dear Mom,
if you're reading this...

26:46.521 --> 26:49.558
...it means I called you
from Hollywood, California.

26:49.817 --> 26:53.861
I left my diary behind because
I want you to see why I'm leaving.

26:54.071 --> 26:55.814
It's not because you hit me.

26:56.073 --> 26:59.157
I hid this so Dave the dickhead
wouldn't find it.

26:59.451 --> 27:01.490
Warren Anderson and me
are in love.

27:01.744 --> 27:03.986
I'm going to start
a new life with him.

27:04.205 --> 27:06.079
His dad owns
that garage in town.

27:06.624 --> 27:09.245
But Warren has even bigger plans.

27:09.501 --> 27:11.458
He'll become a star
in action movies.

27:11.712 --> 27:14.463
He says I'm prettier
than a lot of girls in movies.

27:14.715 --> 27:15.995
I could be a star too.

27:16.425 --> 27:17.836
You want a drink?

27:18.260 --> 27:19.884
When we cruise into Hollywood...

27:20.137 --> 27:24.715
...I'll have fiery eyes that everyone
will notice, because I am in love.

27:27.019 --> 27:29.770
You were right.
I didn't find anything.

27:30.814 --> 27:31.977
Fixed you a drink.

27:32.232 --> 27:34.604
Thanks, no.
I've got work to do.

27:34.860 --> 27:36.769
I'll stop by tomorrow night.

27:37.738 --> 27:40.276
We'll probably be married
by the time you read this.

27:41.658 --> 27:44.030
Don't come looking for me,
because I'm not coming back.

27:44.285 --> 27:47.986
Maybe someday you'll see me
on TV or in magazines.

27:48.247 --> 27:51.414
Don't worry about me.
Love, Mary Anne.

27:51.793 --> 27:53.500
Mr. Anderson?

27:55.755 --> 27:56.585
Who's asking?

27:56.798 --> 27:59.633
Tom Hart.
